# ============================================================
# LIFE.TXT  -  one big text file (OBTF): journal, ideas, notes, and todos,
# in one chronological stream. Structure comes from :tags:, not separate files.
#
# Entry format:   YYYY-MM-DD Day | free text here :tag: :tag:
# Separator:      a *** line between entries (visual only; agenda ignores it).
#
# Tag style: LIFE.TXT uses colon-delimited :tag: tokens, space-separated
# (one token each: :todo: :work:), NOT chained (:todo:work:). The colons
# delimit tags within free-form prose, where @ alone could be ambiguous
# against ordinary words. calendar.txt uses @tag (todo.txt style) instead;
# the difference is intentional - each file follows its own lineage.
#
# How agenda reads this file:
#   open todo      = a line with :todo:    and NOT :done:
#   open waiting   = a line with :waiting: and NOT :done:
#   closed item    = add :done: in place; it then drops out of agenda
#   due follow-up  = add  due:YYYY-MM-DD  to a line; agenda surfaces it LOUD
#                    within its lead window (see: agenda --help)
#
# NOTE: This is a template. Example dates are illustrative - replace with
# your own. Location is adjustable: agenda reads it from $LIFE_DIR
# (default ~/life, so ~/life/LIFE.TXT); set LIFE_DIR to point elsewhere,
# e.g. /mnt/usbflashdrive/life/LIFE.TXT on a machine using a USB drive.
# ============================================================

:tag: CONVENTIONS
---------------------
Tags are keywords enclosed in colons, opened AND closed: :like_this:
Lowercase, underscores for spaces. Every tag opens and closes with a colon.
Tags are space-separated, one token each: :todo: :work: -- NOT chained
  org-mode style (:todo:work:). Deliberate + org-independent: adopting org
  later means a full outline conversion, not a colon-syntax match; a clean
  space-separated file converts more easily, not less. Decided; don't reopen.
State:  :todo: :waiting: :done: :someday: :dropped:
        (grep ':todo:' LIFE.TXT  finds all open actions; swap state as needed)
Area:   :work: :health: :career: :family:
        (grep ':health:' LIFE.TXT  finds all entries in that area)
Kind:   :reference:   non-actionable lookup data (measurements, specs, etc.)
        (grep ':reference:' LIFE.TXT  lists all; agenda ignores these by design)
Project:  :project_NAME:
          (grep -o ':project_[a-z0-9_]*:' LIFE.TXT | sort -u  lists all)
Dated:  :todo: with  due:YYYY-MM-DD   (due: is a key:value token, NOT a tag --
        no surrounding colons, always its own space-separated token)
        (grep 'due:' LIFE.TXT  finds all; grep 'due:2026-' for a year)
No contexts (@home/@errands): tasks aren't location-gated here.
Area covers grouping; reintroduce :context_NAME: only if real
location-batching ever appears.
